					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">I assume you mean pin 26 and not 23 of the 6264... </div><br />Raah, this annoy me. Why am I always writing stuff down wrong ?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">that oughta do it. mod requires 3 wires, for &lt;board A13&gt; -&gt; &lt;62256 pin 26&gt;, &lt;board A14&gt; -&gt; &lt;62256 pin 1&gt;, &lt;board /CE (pin 26)&gt; -&gt; &lt;62256 pin 20&gt; </div>
<br />Yes. In SXROM case, "board A13" would be CHR A14, and "board A14" would be CHR A15. But what about "board /CE" ? This one doesn't exist, because the MMC1 doesn't output anything for pin 23 /CE, but only for pin 26 CE. So if you do it like you said, the WRAM will be enabled when the CPU acess ROM, but disabled when trying to acess RAM. That wouldn't work of course.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
